<h1>@HI{{ze}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @EM{{@HI{{ze}}}}.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ze}}}} is a sentence ending particle that adds force to a sentence. It makes a declaration
to someone or underscores a point. Where its usage is similar, it is slightly less emphatic than
<a href="grammar-particle-zo.html">zo</a>.
It is mostly used by men.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{before}}ni@KJ{{going}}ku@EM{{ze}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'm going on ahead.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

